
Overview of adv justly

The adv justly has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) rightly, justly, justifiedly -- (with honesty; "he was rightly considered the greatest singer of his time")
2. (1) justly, right -- (in accordance with moral or social standards; "that serves him right"; "do right by him")
